<subSubSection id="C3697FF2FF98FFFF92BBD0ADFAAAFCF2" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC2C79FF98FFFF92BBD0ADFE09FDAA" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="B907F06BFF98FFFF92BBD0ADFDF2FF7A" bold="true" box="[199,563,151,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">
Description of 3 
<superScript id="7C068131FF98FFFF93F4D0A0FE56FF6C" attach="left" box="[392,407,151,165]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">rd</superScript>
instar larva.
</emphasis>
Size (based on 
<specimenCount id="9D75E7F0FF98FFFF9097D0ADFCBAFF7A" box="[747,891,154,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" type="generic">2 specimens</specimenCount>
): BL 
<quantity id="4C8B819CFF98FFFF91C0D0ADFBF2FF7B" box="[956,1075,154,179]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.043" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="10.43">10.43 mm</quantity>
; HL 
<quantity id="4C8B819CFF98FFFF9612D0ADFB13FF7B" box="[1134,1234,154,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.21" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="2.21">2.21 mm</quantity>
(2.12–2.30), HW 
<quantity id="4C8B819CFF98FFFF92EBD089FF3CFF1F" box="[151,253,190,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.24" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="3.24">3.24 mm</quantity>
(3.23–3.25), ML 
<quantity id="4C8B819CFF98FFFF93B7D089FDF0FF1F" box="[459,561,190,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="297" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.60 mm</quantity>
(2.59–2.62), HW/HL 1.47, ML/HL 1.17. General colouring ochre with grey markings and spots, ventral side noticeably paler, mottled with grey; dorsal side of the head capsule light brown, ventral side of the head light brown with a dark area on the mouthparts, mandibles brown; legs ochre; setae black, most dolichasters grey. Head rectangular, dorsal side with a narrow posterior depression; long setae are present at the base of the forward-placed ocular tubercles (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF90C8D179FCC6FEAE" box="[692,775,334,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
); mandibles narrow, close at the base (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF96CBD179FAC9FEAE" box="[1207,1288,334,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5c</figureCitation>
), longer than the head capsule (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF931DD145FE75FE42" box="[353,436,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
); basal tooth equidistant between the base of the mandible and median tooth; interdental pseudo-teeth (4–3)(4–3)(0); thin and hair-like dolichasters are present at the base of the mandible; external margin of mandible equipped with short setae, longer toward the base. Pronotum covered with short dolichasters; mesothoracic spiracles black; anterior pair of mesothoracic scoli-like processes very large, bent at 90° (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF9745D1E9FA4EFE3E" box="[1337,1423,478,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
). First pair of abdominal spiracles dorsally disposed, black in colour (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF91DAD235FC38FDD2" box="[934,1017,514,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5e</figureCitation>
); the following seven pairs disposed ventrally; dorsal series of abdominal scolus-like processes positioned on the lower sides of the body, in contact with the substrate (
<figureCitation id="134830FCFF98FFFF9310D27DFE7AFDAA" box="[364,443,586,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[254,1327,215,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[240,1347,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="297">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
